  "text": "The AQL query execution pipeline in ArangoDB flows through several key components:\n\n1. **Parsing Stage** (arangod/Aql/Parser.cpp/h): The query string is parsed by the Parser class using a Flex lexer (tokens.ll) and Bison parser (grammar.y). The parser generates an Abstract Syntax Tree (AST) that represents the query structure.\n\n2. **Optimization Stage** (arangod/Aql/Optimizer.cpp/h): The Optimizer class takes the initial execution plan and applies optimization rules to improve query performance. The Optimizer::createPlans method transforms the AST into optimized execution plans. The optimizer rules are defined in OptimizerRules.cpp and feature rules that can significantly restructure the query plan.\n\n3. **Execution Engine Setup** (arangod/Aql/ExecutionEngine.cpp/h): The ExecutionEngine::instantiateFromPlan method creates the execution engine from the optimized plan. The engine manages the execution blocks and coordinates query execution across the system.\n\n4. **Execution Blocks** (arangod/Aql/ExecutionBlock.cpp/h, ExecutionBlockImpl.h/tpp): ExecutionBlock is the base class for different types of execution nodes. ExecutionBlockImpl.h and ExecutionBlockImpl.tpp contain the template implementations for various executor types. Each block represents a specific operation in the query plan (e.g., filtering, aggregation, collection scanning).\n\n5. **Storage Engine Integration** (arangod/RocksDBEngine/RocksDBCollection.cpp/h): The RocksDBCollection class provides the interface to the storage engine for data retrieval. It implements methods like getAnyIterator and getAllIterator that return iterators over documents in the collection. RocksDBCollection interacts with RocksDB for actual data storage and retrieval.\n\n6. **Transaction Management** (arangod/Transaction/Manager.cpp/h, Methods.cpp/h): The transaction::Manager class manages transaction lifecycle and state. The transaction::Methods class provides the actual transaction operations (read/write). These are coordinated with the storage engine through TransactionState (arangod/StorageEngine/TransactionState.h) and RocksDBTransactionState (arangod/RocksDBEngine/RocksDBTransactionState.h) for RocksDB-specific transaction handling.\n\nThe execution flow is: Parser -> AST -> Optimizer -> ExecutionPlan -> ExecutionEngine -> ExecutionBlocks -> RocksDBCollection (via transaction::Methods) -> RocksDB storage engine."
}

